array: used to store multiple values in a single variable

- array is ordered, indexed
- size: arr.lengh (static variable), must be specified by int or short not long

Note: In Java array is a special type of object whose class is non-existence.
      whenever JVM encounters [], it will create an array object in the memory.

int [] arr = new int[10]
int [] arr = {1,2,3,4,5}